  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6589 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6500 (-4404M) and positive gamma at 6605 (+2869M), dealers are currently in a neutral hedging posture but leaning toward selling pressure as we approach the max positive gamma level. The recent regime flip to PIN suggests dealers have flipped to long gamma positioning, meaning they'll provide stabilizing flows by selling rallies above 6605 and buying dips toward 6500. Key battleground is the 6500-6605 range, with 6746 GEX flip as the critical upside level where dealer behavior would reverse to amplifying flows.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6500-6605 with dealers capping moves in either direction.",
